HEADWORD: Proteidea
<hw>Pro`te*id"e*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Proteus</er>, and <er>-oid</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
order of aquatic amphibians having prominent external gills and four
legs. It includes Proteus and Menobranchus (<gen>Necturus</gen>). Called
also <altname>Proteoidea</altname>, and
<altname>Proteida</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proteiform</ent>⟦br⟧
